OL,3,CMeasuring the scale of Starmer's
OL,4,Cwelfare reform debacle
OL,6,FOn Tuesday, Angela Rayner and Liz
OL,7,FKendall were ringing round Labour MPs
OL,8,Fasking frantically what it would take
OL,9,Fto secure their votes.
OL,11,FIn the end - and at the last moment -
OL,12,Fthe government announced that there
OL,13,Fwould be zero cuts in PIP for the
OL,14,Fforecastable future. The rebels got
OL,15,Feverything they wanted.
OL,17,FThe rump of the bill spends money - on
OL,18,Fup-rating universal credit, on work
OL,19,Fcoaches: it doesn't save a penny.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
