OL,3,CMeasuring the scale of Starmer's
OL,4,Cwelfare reform debacle
OL,6,FEven so, a staggering 49 Labour MPs
OL,7,Fvoted against it, presumably because
OL,8,Fthey simply don't trust Starmer and
OL,9,FReeves.
OL,11,FAnd poor Rachel Reeves in her autumn
OL,12,Fbudget somehow has to find not just
OL,13,Fthe #5bn she lost with this radical
OL,14,Fsurgery on the welfare bill, but
OL,15,Fcountless billions more if she is to
OL,16,Fmeet her self-imposed fiscal targets
OL,17,F(the respected NIESR says she is just
OL,18,F#57bn shy of balance!).
OL,20,FBut the real damage is something else.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
